  "text": "The chromosomal deletion was shown to cover the complete Snca locus. Exon 1 and exon 6 of the gene are 97 kB apart (GenBank AF163865; mouse strain 129/SvJ; [CITATION_1] ) and flank the chromosome 6 marker D6Mit357. However, the deletion was shown not to include loci currently mapped at a distance of only 1 cM to each side of Snca, namely Atoh1 and Atoh2 [CITATION_2] . At present, no other genes are known to be located between Atoh1 and Atoh2.",
